text: The 30th District of the Iowa Senate is located in northeast Iowa, and is currently composed of Black Hawk County. ==Current elected officials== Eric Giddens is the senator currently representing the 30th District. The area of the 30th District contains two Iowa House of Representatives districts: *The 59th District (represented by Bob Kressig) *The 60th District (represented by Dave Williams) The district is also located in Iowa's 1st congressional district, which is represented by Abby Finkenauer. ==Past senators== The district has previously been represented by: *Charles Miller, 1983-1988 *Mark Hagerla, 1989-1992 *Emil Husak, 1993-1996 *Neal Schuerer, 1997-2002 *Mary Kramer, 2003 *Pat Ward, 2004-2012 *Jeff Danielson, 2013-2019 *Eric Giddens 2019-Present ==See also== *Iowa General Assembly *Iowa Senate ==References== 30
